lf and Elanif are the only ones who own our origional accounts.<br><br>It usually comes down to the fact that if the person spent those two years alone powering their own toon, then who gives a rats ass, but if that person was part of a medium-large guild, that guild has probably awarded that person with an awe inspiring amount of loot.<br><br>Now, if real life issues come up and the person ebays to take care of financial issues, the guild is usually understanding.  But if someone like, say, the owner of Raftik, just up and ebays along with alot of shit that he/she was borrowing and less then a week after a guild effort to get his epic goes through like this so called Indra person, then people feel hurt and angry.<br><br>Especially if they don't tell anyone.  It's like telling your guild, "Hey, I"m gonna take a break from EQ" and the next day you're wearing another guilds tag.<br><br>It's ultimately about honesty, loyalty and trust. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35824><img src=http://perfectflaw.wox.org/images/sinfest/selfish.gif></a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upopitinythug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Popi Tinythug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/02 2:37:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1694.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.fortunecity.com/popidathug/poppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is selling your acct such a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> I have nothing against selling an account, but i do find people that pay hundreds for an account stupid...  <p><center>"Rats know the way of rats."<br> <b> Chinese Proverb</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top 