 to ebay.<br><br>Right after getting a Nice peice of loot and not using it to help the other 40 people who helped you get it get THEIR piece of loot = BAD time to ebay.<br><br>The BIG trouble with ebay, of course, is that you no longer have any protection whatsoever if something goes wrong with the account.  All ebayed accounts are succeptable to sudden banning by their original owners getting ornery and bitching to verant.  This makes letting loot go to toons whose accounts are ebayed a risk, as there are significant odds that it might go poof just as much as if you had let it rot....better to let it go to a non ebayed account.<br><br>In my opinion, the only accounts worth paying for are 50+ druids and shamen and chanters (and perhaps cleric with stick or 56+) who you can use to 2box characters on an account you DO own.  Why? Because they are useful unequiped and can rapidly get any alt yer thinking about up to speed, or help a buddy get out of the lower levels.  Ebays as mains....well, I can see their use on a GUILD level, to insure that mandatory classes aren't missing, for an addict level player who is on all the time.<br><br>Whatever, I'll never ebay... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umalse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/02 4:53:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1694.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is selling your acct such a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>I play for the benefit of the guild so we can do new stuff. If that means farming stuff like AoW, which offers no loot of interest to me, to equip our warriors enough to take us to the next level, you're darn right I'll be there. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>No personal slight intended, but pragmatism and patience is not a substitute for honor.<br><br>There are individuals in any guild like that, usually the core group that's been with the guild the whole time, through thick and thin. Or someone who joined as a friend of that core. However, you couldn't get me doped up enough to buy that most of the people who join an active raiding guild are doing it &quot;for the experience.&quot;<br><br>Most people play the fastest path to their loot they can find. That's how guilds like IvM happen -- there is no way they would have gotten the same recruitment mass if they were not initially one of the guilds most capable of acquiring loot fast. That doesn't mean everyone there is some item-crazed ebay fanatic, but no one is dumb enough to believe they're all a bunch of angels of virtue either.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usodseller123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sodseller123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/02 6:22:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1694.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is selling your acct such a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> Well I think it is ok to ebay your character if you do it in a non greedy way such as stealing loot before you go or getting your epic then selling it right after, but some people use this game to support them selves and hey if they can manipulate the game that well then Kudos to them. Lets take it to the next level though , what about ebaying plat and items? If you think about it there has to be some of those huge guilds selling stuff since there are very few people on the server who have good enough loot to sell tormax loot , warder loot, yelinak loot etc etc. Is it wrong to buy and sell platinum or items if you play your character just as well, but makes yours character better? It is really an opinion on weather you think its write or wrong. If I remember correctly verant use to allow this but I am not sure and will not get into that, but if verant was smart they would to keep more people playing since UO is still going strong due to the fact they allow this and not let characters and accounts rot. I know for a fact at least 70% of people or more between all servers ebay since if that wasnt true there would not be such a big market with like 20,000 items or more for sale weekly. Most people dislike it when they are not doing it, but once they start doing it they have no problem with it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uselwensoulgazer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Selwen Soulgazer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ayonae Vice</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/02 10:01:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1694.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.colba.net/~xtlee/images/fistc03.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is selling your acct such a bad thing?</span><hr size=1> PSychojetpilot,if you new Darkmelusine like some of us do,that statement you made would seem rediculous.She is an extremely unselfish person.<br> There are a lot of people in EW that are very unselfish as well.I've seen many of them pass on some great loot so that their guildmates could thrive.They arent in the high end game to get loot,they are there to help each other succeed.That kind of selfishness is why they continue to do great things and remain as solid guild. <p>   <font color= ffoooo>Selwen SoulGazer</font > <BR>High P